pepper /ˈpɛpə/

(peppering,peppered,peppers) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Pepper or black pepper is a hot-tasting spice used to flavour food. 胡椒 

例： Season with salt and pepper. 用盐和胡椒调味。 

2. N-COUNT A pepper , or a bell pepper , is a hollow green, red, or yellow vegetable with seeds inside it. 椒类 

例： ...2 red or green peppers, sliced. …2个切成片了的红椒或青椒。 

3. V-T If something is peppered with small objects, a lot of those objects hit it. (以小物体) 大量击中 [usu passive] 

例： He was wounded in both legs and severely peppered with shrapnel. 他两条腿都受伤了，受到了弹片重创。

